    <!-- Chart Explanations -->
    <string name="chart_explanation_distribution_title">What is Emotion Distribution?</string>
    <string name="chart_explanation_distribution_content">Emotion distribution shows the proportion of various emotions in your records within the selected time range. This helps you understand your emotional patterns, which emotions are your primary emotions, and which emotions appear less frequently.</string>
    <string name="chart_insight_distribution">According to your data, happy emotion accounts for the highest proportion (40%), indicating that you are generally a positive and optimistic person.</string>
    
    <string name="chart_explanation_trend_title">What is Emotion Trend?</string>
    <string name="chart_explanation_trend_content">Emotion trend shows how your emotional intensity changes over time. By observing the trend line, you can understand the fluctuations of your emotions, identify peaks and valleys in your emotions, and possible factors that may affect your emotions.</string>
    <string name="chart_insight_trend">Your emotion trend shows that emotions peak on Wednesdays, while emotions are lower on Tuesdays. This may be related to your work schedule or social activities.</string>
    
    <string name="chart_explanation_patterns_title">What are Emotion Patterns?</string>
    <string name="chart_explanation_patterns_content">Emotion patterns are regularities and trends discovered by analyzing your emotional data. These patterns may be related to time, weather, weekdays, and other factors, helping you better understand the patterns of your emotional changes.</string>
    <string name="chart_insight_patterns">Your data shows that emotions are usually more positive in the morning, while evenings are calmer. This indicates that your emotional changes have certain daily patterns.</string>
    
    <string name="chart_explanation_comparison_title">What is Emotion Comparison?</string>
    <string name="chart_explanation_comparison_content">Emotion comparison shows the proportion changes of various emotions in different periods (such as this week vs. last week). Through comparative analysis, you can understand the trend of your emotional changes and identify improvements or deteriorations in your emotions.</string>
    <string name="chart_insight_comparison" formatted="false">Compared to last week, your happy emotion increased by 10% this week, while calm emotion decreased by 10%. This may indicate that you experienced more exciting things this week.</string>
    
